  "prompt": "Can I apply for an E-2 visa while my green card is on process?",
  "response": "Generally, applying for an E-2 visa while your green card is in process can be complicated. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Potential Conflicts:\n- E-2 visa is a non-immigrant visa\n- Green card process indicates immigrant intent\n- These can sometimes be seen as conflicting goals\n\n2. Possible Scenarios:\n- If your green card is pending adjustment of status, an E-2 might raise concerns\n- You may need to demonstrate that you still intend to return to your home country\n- Consular officers might question your immigration intentions\n\n3. Recommendations:\n- Consult an immigration attorney for personalized advice\n- Your specific circumstances will determine feasibility\n- Provide clear documentation explaining your situation\n- Be prepared to explain how the E-2 fits into your overall immigration strategy\n\n4. Risks:\n- Potential complications with your green card application\n- Possibility of being seen as having conflicting immigration intentions\n\n5. Best Practice:\n- Seek professional legal guidance specific to your case\n- Have a clear, documented explanation for your visa application\n\nNote: Immigration laws can be complex and subject to change. Consulting an experienced immigration attorney is strongly recommended for your specific situation.",
